<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="b3fcb63f-7f1d-550f-8fcb-e045b5cc86e0" activityNameId="ac1e5cd4-4742-45d0-9514-319520f651ea" parentActivityId="f02b40f1-d518-4cb3-af47-a6086394bd14" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">sodium tetrafluoroborate production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">tetrafluoro-,sodium</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">sodiumborontetrafluoride</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">sodium fluoborate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">borate(1-)</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">sodium fluoroborate</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">sodium borofluoride</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The dataset starts with the reception of sodium fluoride and boron trifluoride at plant.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The dataset ends with the production of tetrafluoroborate.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset presents the production of tetrafluoroborate as a result of reacting boron trifluoride and sodium fluoride. Yield is estimated as 95%.  No emissions are considered due to toxic nature of emitted chemicals and therefore are assumed to be recovered. Infrastructure, energy and water use are based on standard assumptions for chemical inventories.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="34dbbff8-88ce-11de-ad60-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">GLO</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">based on stoichiometric reaction</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The reaction is designed for eliminating BF3 from a gaseous stream mix with reactive hydrocarbons (olefin hydrocarbons) by its conversion into sodium tetrafluoroborate. The process takes place by passing the gaseous stream in contact with sodium fluoride in the presence of small quantitites of a dialkyl ether, preferably diethyl esther. The ether acts as a catalyst. The reaction yield is stated to be high. We estimate a yield of 95% since no specific data is given.  Other methal halides can substitute the NaF in the present reaction, such as calcium fluoride and aluminium fluoride. The stoichiometric equation is: NaF + BF3 = NaBF4</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">It should be noted that this is not the main route for producing sodium tetrafluoroborate. The standard production route involves the neutralisation of tetrafluoroboric acid with sodium carbonate or sodium hydroxide. The present reaction is used for eliminating the catalytic action of boron trifluoride, present in gaseous streams containing reactive olefin hydrocarbons, such as isobutylene, which is an intermediary for producing additives for lubricants and fuels. This process is applied in the fields of natural gas and petroleum processing.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2002-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">based on latest published literature (refer to published source)</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
